    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-10-21T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-10-21T11:00:00-05:00" n="410" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d410">
                <head>No. 405.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Curry</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-10-21T11:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 21,
                                1886—11 a.m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Bayard informs Mr. Curry that he is instructed to state to the Government
                        of Spain that the accommodation of all differences is equally and earnestly
                        desired by the President, and that, if notified that the Spanish Government
                        will levy no discrimination against American vessels and cargoes which, they
                        carry from the United States or any foreign country, the proclamation of
                        1884 will be renewed by him.</p>
            </div>
